                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; incipit of the miracles; four groups
                           of lines on the incipit page of the Text I-1 (fol. 3a) alternating with
                           black lines; the words ʾǝsaggǝd la-malakotǝka (or the word ʾǝsaggǝd only)
                           in Text I-1; incipit of the verses in the Text I-2; miralcle numbers in
                           Text I-3; incipit of the sections in Text I-3; elements of the
                           punctuation signs; elements of Ethiopic numerals; two lines in the middle
                           of fol. 10va</seg>
                     </handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h2" script="Ethiopic">The size of the script significantly
                        varies throughout the Ms.: cp. fols. in the beginning of the Ms., <locus target="#33r">33r</locus> and 33v, 58v and 59r, 76v and 77r, esp.
                        124r.</handNote>
